<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="75" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,861,1249]" pageId="20" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,294,1006,1032]" pageId="20" pageNumber="75">Ecology</emphasis>
. Poorly known, deep-water species, depth range: 
<quantity box="[858,971,1006,1033]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.35" metricValueMax="11.9" metricValueMin="2.8" pageId="20" pageNumber="75" unit="m" value="73.5" valueMax="119.0" valueMin="28.0">28–119 m</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Ramos-Porto, M. &amp; Coelho, P. A." box="[986,1321,1006,1032]" pageId="20" pageNumber="75" pagination="181 - 189" refId="ref24150" refString="Ramos-Porto, M. &amp; Coelho, P. A. (1993) Sinopse dos crustaceos decapodos brasileiros (familia Hippolytidae). Trabalhos Oceanograficos da Universidade Federal de Pernambuco, 22, 181 - 189. https: // doi. org / 10.5914 / tropocean. v 22 i 1.2663" type="journal article" year="1993">Ramos-Porto &amp; Coelho 1993</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Rhyne, A. L. &amp; Lin, J." pageId="20" pageNumber="75" pagination="165 - 204" refId="ref24370" refString="Rhyne, A. L. &amp; Lin, J. (2006) A western Atlantic peppermint shrimp complex: redescription of Lysmata wurdemanni, description of four new species, and remarks on Lysmata rathbunae (Crustacea: Decapoda: Hippolytidae). Bulletin of Marine Science, 79, 165 - 204." type="journal article" year="2006">Rhyne &amp; Lin 2006</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="75" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,861,1249]" pageId="20" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1078,1104]" pageId="20" pageNumber="75">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chace" authorityYear="1970" box="[322,537,1078,1104]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rathbunae">
<emphasis box="[322,537,1078,1104]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="75">Lysmata rathbunae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a species found in relatively deep waters, ranging from 
<quantity box="[1187,1319,1078,1105]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.35" metricValueMax="11.9" metricValueMin="2.8" pageId="20" pageNumber="75" unit="m" value="73.5" valueMax="119.0" valueMin="28.0">28 to 119 m</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Rhyne, A. L. &amp; Lin, J." pageId="20" pageNumber="75" pagination="165 - 204" refId="ref24370" refString="Rhyne, A. L. &amp; Lin, J. (2006) A western Atlantic peppermint shrimp complex: redescription of Lysmata wurdemanni, description of four new species, and remarks on Lysmata rathbunae (Crustacea: Decapoda: Hippolytidae). Bulletin of Marine Science, 79, 165 - 204." type="journal article" year="2006">Rhyne &amp; Lin 2006</bibRefCitation>
), and is readily recognised by its very long rostrum, which overreaches the antennular peduncle. The species was first recorded in 
<collectingCountry box="[433,501,1150,1176]" name="Brazil" pageId="20" pageNumber="75">Brazil</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ramos-Porto, M. &amp; Coelho, P. A." box="[542,887,1150,1177]" pageId="20" pageNumber="75" pagination="181 - 189" refId="ref24150" refString="Ramos-Porto, M. &amp; Coelho, P. A. (1993) Sinopse dos crustaceos decapodos brasileiros (familia Hippolytidae). Trabalhos Oceanograficos da Universidade Federal de Pernambuco, 22, 181 - 189. https: // doi. org / 10.5914 / tropocean. v 22 i 1.2663" type="journal article" year="1993">Ramos-Porto &amp; Coelho (1993)</bibRefCitation>
, based on material collected at 
<quantity box="[1234,1290,1150,1177]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" pageId="20" pageNumber="75" unit="m" value="28.0">28 m</quantity>
depth off the coast of 
<collectingRegion box="[244,339,1186,1212]" country="Brazil" name="Alagoas" pageId="20" pageNumber="75">Alagoas</collectingRegion>
. In 
<bibRefCitation author="Coelho, P. A. &amp; Almeida, A. O. &amp; Souza-Filho, J. F. &amp; Bezerra, L. E. A. &amp; Giraldes, B. W." box="[380,610,1186,1213]" pageId="20" pageNumber="75" pagination="41 - 62" refId="ref21848" refString="Coelho, P. A., Almeida, A. O., Souza-Filho, J. F., Bezerra, L. E. A. &amp; Giraldes, B. W. (2006) Diversity and distribution of the marine and estuarine shrimps (Dendrobranchiata, Stenopodidea and Caridea) from North and Northeast Brazil. Zootaxa, 1221 (1), 41 - 62. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 1221.1.5" type="journal article" year="2006">
Coelho 
<emphasis box="[468,525,1186,1212]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="75">et al.</emphasis>
(2006)
</bibRefCitation>
’s checklist, the species is also listed from 
<collectingRegion box="[1081,1224,1186,1212]" country="Brazil" name="Pernambuco" pageId="20" pageNumber="75">Pernambuco</collectingRegion>
, presumably based on specimens deposited in the collection of the Universidade Federal de 
<collectingRegion box="[964,1107,1222,1248]" country="Brazil" name="Pernambuco" pageId="20" pageNumber="75">Pernambuco</collectingRegion>
, Recife, 
<collectingCountry box="[1205,1273,1222,1248]" name="Brazil" pageId="20" pageNumber="75">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(UFPE).
</paragraph>
